import * as React from 'react' import './pageNine.css' import Title from './components/title_bar' import Navbar from './components/nav_bar' import Font from './components/fnt_sze' export default function History(){ const [Lang,SetLang] = React.useState('EN'); let LangEN,LangDE; if(Lang === 'EN'){ LangEN = 'block' LangDE = 'none' } else if (Lang === 'DE'){ LangDE='block' LangEN='none' } const [Fntsze,SetFntsze]=React.useState(20) return(
<Navbar onUpdate={(value:string)=>SetLang(value)} pg_History='4px solid red'/> <div className = 'txt_box'> <h1 style={{display:LangEN}}>History</h1> <h1 style={{display:LangDE}}>Geschichte</h1> <Font fntSlct={(sze:number)=>SetFntsze(sze)}/> <hr></hr> <p style={{display:LangEN,fontSize:Fntsze}}> The first constitutional meeting of the International Club Juelich e.V. took place on March 8, 1970. <br></br> <br></br> The first committee board had seven members namely, Mrs. R. Kamat, Dr. Wald, Mr. Ahrens, Mr. Kedim, Mr. Galikine, Dr. Fischer and the town magistrate Mr . Schroeder. <br></br> <br></br> The club's constitution was accepted on Feb.15, 1972 and on March 24, 1972, the club was entered into the Register of Associations at the Juelich local court. At this time, the club has approximately 110 members, from twenty different countries. <br></br> <br></br> The first meetings were held at the "Old Town Hall", then shifted to the old engineering school (now the Fachhochschule), and finally at the Roncalli-Haus, until the construction of the guest house was completed in 1972. </p> </div> </div> ) }
